last_episode_to_air.name: Grand Finale
last_episode_to_air.overview: The top queens face off in an epic evening of performances and lip syncs, as they compete for the title of America’s Next Drag Superstar and a grand prize of $200,000.

name: RuPaul's Drag Race
overview: Join RuPaul, the world's most famous drag queen, as the host, mentor and judge for the ultimate in drag queen competitions. The top drag queens in the U.S. will vie for drag stardom as RuPaul, in full glamazon drag, will reign supreme in all judging and eliminations while helping guide the contestants as they prepare for each challenge.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: Nine contestants were selected to compete in the running of becoming "America's Next Drag Superstar". The winner of the first season won the following prizes: a lifetime supply of MAC Cosmetics, be featured an LA Eyeworks campaign, join the Logo Drag Race tour, and a cash prize of $20,000.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: For season two, the number of contestants was increased from nine to twelve, and the prizes were slightly modified: a lifetime supply of Nyx Cosmetics and be the face of nyxcosmetics.com, an exclusive one year public relations contract with LGBT firm Project Publicity, be featured an LA Eyeworks campaign, join the Logo Drag Race tour, and a cash prize of $25,000.

seasons.name: Season 3
seasons.overview:
The third season of RuPaul's Drag Race began airing on January 24, 2011. Thirteen drag queens competed for the title of "America's Next Drag Superstar", a headlining spot on the Absolut Tour, a lifetime supply of Kryolan makeup, and a cash prize of $75,000.

This season saw Michelle Visage replacing Merle Ginsberg at the judge's table and Billy B., Mike Ruiz, and Jeffrey Moran filling in for Santino Rice's absence during several episodes.

seasons.name: Season 4
seasons.overview: The winner of season four will headline Logo's Drag Race Tour featuring Absolut Vodka, wins a one-of-a-kind trip, a lifetime supply of NYX Cosmetics, a cash prize of $100,000, and the title of "America's Next Drag Superstar."

seasons.name: Season 5
seasons.overview: The fifth season of RuPaul's Drag Race began airing on January 28, 2013, with a 90-minute premiere episode. The winner of season five headlined Logo's Drag Race Tour featuring Absolut Vodka, won a one-of-a-kind trip, a lifetime supply of Colorevolution Cosmetics, and a cash prize of $100,000.

seasons.name: Season 6
seasons.overview: Just when you thought you knew what to expect from RuPaul’s Drag Race, along comes the ferociously fabulous and funny Season Six, with enough tricks up its silk chiffon sleeve to keep you on your painted toes! This crop of queens is our most diverse yet, from seasoned pros, to an international drag star, to a former American Idol contestant, and even some fresh-faced ingénue queens who were inspired to be drag performers by watching Season One of RuPaul’s Drag Race! That’s one leggy legacy. Have we mentioned that these boys are hot? Because they are. Have we mentioned they make even hotter women? Because they do.

seasons.name: Season 7
seasons.overview: ​​​RuPaul's Drag Race returns with a court of queens so ingenious, a competition so unpredictable and a judges' panel so packed with talent, you'll be seeing stars It's all the artistry, all the humanity and all the head-turning twists you love but if you think you know this Race, honey, you have no idea.​​

seasons.name: Season 8
seasons.overview: RuPaul is back to light up the runway with 12 new queens competing for the title of "American's Next Drag Superstar." Season 8 marks a drag milestone: the 100th episode and the 100th queen! Watch as these talented ladies of drag join the ranks of the fabulous 88 queens who fought for the crown before them. The 12 Queens to compete include: Acid Betty, Bob the Drag Queen, Chi Chi DeVayne, Cynthia Lee Fontaine, Dax ExclamationPoint, Derrick Barry, Kim Chi, Laila McQueen, Naomi Smalls, Nayasha Lopez, Robbie Turner, and Thorgy Thor.

seasons.name: Season 9
seasons.overview: Season Nine’s drag queens are fiercer than ever, competing to snatch the coveted title of "America's Next Drag Superstar." This year’s cutthroat race to the crown features unpredictable competition, gag-worthy performances, and jaw-dropping moments.

seasons.name: Season 10
seasons.overview: The tenth season of RuPaul's Drag Race began airing on March 22, 2018, on VH1. The premiere was broadcast one week after the finale of the third season of RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars, and episodes are to be followed by RuPaul's Drag Race: Untucked.

seasons.name: Season 11
seasons.overview: RuPaul's Drag Race and Untucked return with more sickening styles, fierce challenges and backstage drama. Michelle Visage, Carson Kressley, Ross Mathews and celeb guest judges join RuPaul as she sets out to crown America's Next Drag Superstar.

seasons.name: Season 12
seasons.overview: The twelfth season of RuPaul's Drag Race premiered on February 28 and concluded on May 29, 2020. The competition was broadcast on VH1 in the United States and saw 13 new queens competing for the title of "America's Next Drag Superstar".

seasons.name: Season 13
seasons.overview: The thirteenth season of RuPaul's Drag Race premiered on January 1 and concluded on April 23, 2021. The cast was announced via Twitter on December 9, 2020. The competition is broadcast on VH1 in the United States and showcases 13 new queens competing for the title of "America's Next Drag Superstar".

seasons.name: Season 14
seasons.overview: The fourteenth season of RuPaul's Drag Race premiered on January 7, 2022. The reality competition series, broadcast on VH1 in the United States, showcases 14 new queens competing for the title of "America's Next Drag Superstar".

seasons.name: Season 15
seasons.overview: This season features the largest cast in the show's history, with sixteen queens competing and the largest cash prize, with the winner earning $200,000. It is also the first season to feature biological relatives, twins Sugar and Spice. Series judges Michelle Visage, Carson Kressley, and Ross Mathews returned, and Ts Madison, who had previously appeared as a recurring guest judge, joined the rotating judges panel.

seasons.name: Season 16
seasons.overview: The sixteenth season of Drag Race showcases fourteen drag queens competing for the title of America's Next Drag Superstar, a one-year supply of Anastasia Beverly Hills cosmetics, a crown and scepter from Fierce Drag Jewels and a cash prize of $200,000.

episodes.name: Drag on a Dime
episodes.overview: Nine contestants must re-invent their glam drag looks using thrift store clothing and tschotchkes from the 99-cent store. Guest judge Bob Mackie stops by to help RuPaul weed out the drag queen with the least style.

episodes.name: Girl Group Challenge
episodes.overview: Wigs fly when the contestants split up into 2 rival girl groups, something guest judge Michelle Williams of Destiny's Child would know plenty about. Can the girls impress RuPaul with their lip-synching skills?

episodes.name: Queens of All Media
episodes.overview: The queens are tested on their multi-media prowess as they show off their talents as newscaster, product spokesperson, and talk show host to RuPaul and guest judge Debra Wilson of MADtv.

episodes.name: MAC/Viva Glam Challenge
episodes.overview: Hoping to follow in the footsteps of MAC Cosmetics' first Viva Glam girl, RuPaul, the queens make their own Viva Glam screen test. Jenny Shimizu joins the panel to help judge the girls' drag queen status.

episodes.name: Drag School of Charm
episodes.overview: The contestants make over a group of female extreme fighters into their drag daughters. Xena herself, Lucy Lawless, makes a guest appearance to judge the girls' combat prowess.

episodes.name: Absolut Drag Ball
episodes.overview: RuPaul makes the queens hit the floor in a good old fashioned drag ball inspired by Absolut's real fruit flavored vodkas.

episodes.name: Extra Special Edition
episodes.overview: Look back at the highlights, lowlights, and previously unseen footage from the first six episodes as we race toward the climactic grand finale!

episodes.name: Grand Finale
episodes.overview: The last 3 queens face their final challenge while shooting the music video for RuPaul's new single "Cover Girl (Put The Bass In Your Walk)." Out artist Cazwell stops by to help the judges cast their final vote.

episodes.name: Reunited!
episodes.overview: In this reunion special, all nine contestants return to give their take on what happened during the show. Plus, the girls confront the judges...and each other!

guest_stars.name: Elena Gant

episodes.name: Shady Politics
episodes.overview: The queens shoot shady presidential campaign ads, throwing their wigs in the ring to become the first drag president of the USA. Vivica A. Fox (Independence Day: Resurgence) and MSNBC Live news anchor Thomas Roberts guest judge.

episodes.name: RuPaul Book Ball
episodes.overview: The queens compete in a pageant of book inspired couture, and perform a musical tribute to Jerri Blank from Strangers With Candy. Siblings Amy Sedaris and David Sedaris guest judge.

episodes.name: The Realness
episodes.overview: The queens compete in their final challenge - starring in the music video for RuPaul's hit "The Realness." Michelle Visage, Carson Kressley and Ross Mathews judge.

episodes.name: Grand Finale
episodes.overview: Tensions run high as the queens return to discuss the drama of the season. Plus, both "America's Next Drag Superstar" and "Miss Congeniality" are crowned.

8.name: Season 8
8.overview: RuPaul is back to light up the runway with 12 new queens competing for the title of "American's Next Drag Superstar." Season 8 marks a drag milestone: the 100th episode and the 100th queen! Watch as these talented ladies of drag join the ranks of the fabulous 88 queens who fought for the crown before them. The 12 Queens to compete include: Acid Betty, Bob the Drag Queen, Chi Chi DeVayne, Cynthia Lee Fontaine, Dax ExclamationPoint, Derrick Barry, Kim Chi, Laila McQueen, Naomi Smalls, Nayasha Lopez, Robbie Turner, and Thorgy Thor.

episodes.name: Oh. My. Gaga!
episodes.overview: Lady Gaga drops by to meet the 13 new queens competing to become America's Next Drag Superstar. Their first test is to compete in the Miss Charisma Uniqueness Nerve and Talent pageant.

episodes.name: She Done Already Done Brought It On
episodes.overview: Lisa Kudrow from Friends stops by, and the queens are challenged to perform in an epic cheer battle. With guest judges The B-52s.

episodes.name: Draggily Ever After
episodes.overview: The queens must create fairytale drag princesses, and transform themselves into sassy sidekicks. With guest judges Todrick Hall and Cheyenne Jackson (American Horror Story).

episodes.name: Good Morning Bitches
episodes.overview: The queens join the cutthroat Morning Talk Show wars. Naya Rivera (Glee) and Jeffrey Bowyer-Chapman (UnREAL) guest judge.

episodes.name: Reality Stars: The Musical
episodes.overview: Todrick Hall directs the queens in Broadway's newest mega-sensation, a Reality Stars musical. Singer Meghan Trainor guest judges.

episodes.name: Snatch Game
episodes.overview: The queens impersonate celebrities in a quick-witted TV game show. With guest judges Candis Cayne and Denis O’Hare (American Horror Story).

episodes.name: 9021-HO
episodes.overview: The queens act in a classic 90s high school drama, directed by original Beverly Hills 90210 stars Tori Spelling and Jennie Garth.

episodes.name: RuPaul Roast
episodes.overview: The queens perform a comedy roast of RuPaul in front of a live audience. Singer Tamar Braxton and Fortune Feimster (The Mindy Project) guest judge.

episodes.name: Your Pilot's On Fire
episodes.overview: The queens create, write and star in their own TV pilots. Noah Galvin (The Real O’Neals) and QVC queen Lisa Robertson guest judge.

episodes.name: Makeovers: Crew Better Work
episodes.overview: The queens makeover members of the Drag Race crew. Singer Kesha and RuPaul’s gown designer Zaldy guest judge.

guest_stars.character: Self - Makeover Crew / Rye Anne Stardust
guest_stars.name: Ryan Brady

guest_stars.character: Self - Makeover Crew / Ariana Bo'Nina Brown
guest_stars.name: Aaron Rand

episodes.name: Gayest Ball Ever
episodes.overview: The queens compete in a queer culture pageant, and design outfits inspired by the Village People. Actress Andie MacDowell (Groundhog Day) and supermodel Joan Smalls guest judge.

episodes.name: Category Is
episodes.overview: The queens must write and perform a rap on RuPaul’s new hit single, and guest on RuPaul’s podcast with Michelle Visage. Style superstar Carson Kressley and the hilarious Ross Mathews guest judge.

episodes.name: Reunion
episodes.overview: As this drag race comes to an end the queens get together to take a look back at who slayed the competition and who deserved to sashey away.

episodes.name: Grand Finale
episodes.overview: In an epic, show-stopping finale, RuPaul crowns America’s Next Drag Superstar.

9.name: Season 9
9.overview: Season Nine’s drag queens are fiercer than ever, competing to snatch the coveted title of "America's Next Drag Superstar." This year’s cutthroat race to the crown features unpredictable competition, gag-worthy performances, and jaw-dropping moments.

episodes.name: 10s Across The Board
episodes.overview: Christina Aguilera stunts on the mainstage. Plus, fan favorite queens from the past decade of Drag Race return as 14 new queens compete to become America’s Next Drag Superstar and win $100,000.

episodes.name: PharmaRusical
episodes.overview: The queens must wow the judges (including Halsey and Padma Lakshmi) in a lip-synced dance number inspired by pharmaceutical TV ads, and Andy Cohen and Alyssa Edwards drop by.

episodes.name: Tap That App
episodes.overview: The queens create and star in commercials for new drag-themed dating apps, and rock goddess Courtney Love and actor Nico Tortorella guest judge.

episodes.name: The Last Ball on Earth
episodes.overview: The queens cook up global warming-friendly looks for the last ball ever, and actresses Tisha Campbell-Martin and Logan Browning drop by to guest judge.

episodes.name: The Bossy Rossy Show
episodes.overview: The queens' improv skills are put to the test for the new talk show "Bossy Rossy," hosted by Ross Matthews, and country music icon Shania Twain and actress Carrie Preston guest judge.

episodes.name: Drag Con Panel Extravaganza
episodes.overview: The queens have to produce and host their very own DragCon panels on makeup, hair and body, and Kumail Nanjiani and Emily V. Gordon guest judge.

episodes.name: Snatch Game
episodes.overview: The queens must impersonate celebrities for the legendary Snatch Game. Audra McDonald and Kate Upton guest judge, and Bianca Del Rio and Alex Trebek are special guests.

episodes.name: The Unauthorized Rusical
episodes.overview: The queens pay tribute to one of the greatest stars of all time in Cher: The Unauthorized Rusical. Andrew Rannells and Billy Eichner guest judge.

episodes.name: Breastworld
episodes.overview: The queens are assigned parts in the new hit series "Breastworld." Broad City stars Ilana Glazer and Abbi Jacobson guest judge, and Randy Rainbow and Stephen Colbert drop by.

episodes.name: Social Media Kings Into Queens
episodes.overview: The queens give some of today's hottest social media superstars drag makeovers. "13 Reasons Why" star Miles Heizer and hip-hop artist Lizzo guest judge.

episodes.name: Evil Twins
episodes.overview: The queens must present two characters on the runway: their best selves and their evil twins. "Girls" creator Lena Dunham and singer Ashanti guest judge, and Cheyenne Jackson ("American Horror Story") is a special guest.

episodes.name: American
episodes.overview: The top four queens must write and perform a verse from RuPaul's hit single "American," and choreographer Todrick Hall, Carson Kressley and Ross Mathews guest judge.

episodes.name: Queens Reunited
episodes.overview: The Season 10 queens return to discuss the most gag-worthy moments, never-before-seen footage, jaw-dropping revelations and the season's most amazing looks.

episodes.name: Grand Finale
episodes.overview: The top four queens get ready to Lip Sync for the Crown in the Season 10 finale.

10.name: Season 10
10.overview: The tenth season of RuPaul's Drag Race began airing on March 22, 2018, on VH1. The premiere was broadcast one week after the finale of the third season of RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars, and episodes are to be followed by RuPaul's Drag Race: Untucked.

episodes.name: Whatcha Unpackin?
episodes.overview: To kick off Season 11, the contestants direct their own photo shoots with Drag Race alumni and design outfits from past queens' materials, and Miley Cyrus guest judges.

episodes.name: Good God Girl, Get Out
episodes.overview: The queens test their acting chops in parody skits of "Black Panther" and "Get Out," and Bobby Moynihan and Sydelle Noel sit in on the judges' panel.

episodes.name: Diva Worship
episodes.overview: The queens put their knowledge of pop icons to the test in a live, evangelical-style talk show about their favorite divas, and Troye Sivan and Guillermo Diaz guest judge.

episodes.name: Trump: The Rusical
episodes.overview: The queens get political when they're asked to read the news with Rachel Maddow and perform a musical about Donald Trump, and Tiffany Pollard and Joel McHale guest judge.

episodes.name: Monster Ball
episodes.overview: The queens put their design skills to the test as they create three different looks for a spooky, monster-themed ball, and Cara Delevingne and Elvira join the judges' panel.

episodes.name: The Draglympics
episodes.overview: Love Connie leads a quick-drag workout, the queens compete in Draglympic floor routines, and choreographer Travis Wall and Olympians Adam Rippon and Mirai Nagasu guest judge.

episodes.name: From Farm to Runway
episodes.overview: The queens use organic ingredients to create sickening but sustainable looks, Alyssa Edwards choreographs a hoedown, and Amber Valletta and Kandi Burruss guest judge.

episodes.name: Snatch Game At Sea
episodes.overview: Morgan McMichaels and Jinkx Monsoon drop into the werk room, and the queens compete in a nautical-themed version of Snatch Game with guest judges Tony Hale and Clea DuVall.

episodes.name: LADP!
episodes.overview: RuPaul opens the library for some reading, the queens star in a "Cops"-style reality show, and Fortune Feimster, Cheyenne Jackson and Natasha Lyonne join the judges.

episodes.name: Dragracadabra
episodes.overview: Delta Work drops by, the queens get into groups and put on their very own magic shows, and Gina Rodriguez and Katherine Langford sit in with the judges.

episodes.name: Bring Back My Queens!
episodes.overview: The girls make over returning queens to look like members of their own drag families, and Lena Waithe and Wanda Sykes guest judge.

episodes.name: Queens Everywhere
episodes.overview: For their last challenge before the grand finale, the Top 5 queens write lyrics to RuPaul's song "Queens Everywhere," perform a dance number and record a podcast interview.

episodes.name: Reunited
episodes.overview: The Season 11 queens reunite to discuss the Brooke Lynn Hytes-Vanessa Vanjie Mateo romance, Ra'Jah O'Hara's salty comments, and Plastique Tiara's changing stories.

episodes.name: Grand Finale
episodes.overview: In the Season 11 grand finale, Christine and the Queens performs, the Top Four girls compete in an epic lip-sync smackdown, and RuPaul crowns America's next drag superstar.

11.name: Season 11
11.overview: RuPaul's Drag Race and Untucked return with more sickening styles, fierce challenges and backstage drama. Michelle Visage, Carson Kressley, Ross Mathews and celeb guest judges join RuPaul as she sets out to crown America's Next Drag Superstar.

episodes.name: I'm That Bitch
episodes.overview: Kicking off Season 12, the first seven queens strut the runway in a fashion show, then rap and perform a choreographed dance in front of guest judge Nicki Minaj.

episodes.name: You Don't Know Me
episodes.overview: In part two of the Season 12 premiere, a new set of queens walks in a fashion show, then performs a Bob Fosse-inspired number in front of guest judges Thandie Newton and Robyn.

episodes.name: World's Worst
episodes.overview: The queens compete on a parody talent show called "World's Worst" and then walk the runway in buttons and bows, and Olivia Munn sits in at the judges' table.

episodes.name: The Ball Ball
episodes.overview: The queens hit the sewing machines to design three different sports-inspired runway lewks for the Ball Ball, and comedian and superfan Leslie Jones sits in with the judges.

episodes.name: Gay’s Anatomy
episodes.overview: The queens put their overacting chops to the test in a "Grey's Anatomy" parody sketch and then walk the runway in cape-forward fashions, and Normani sits in with the judges.

episodes.name: Snatch Game
episodes.overview: The queens compete in the legendary Snatch Game. Mean Girls co-stars Jonathan Bennett and Daniel Franzese guest judge. Drag queen Vanessa Vanjie Mateo (Miss Vanjie) makes a guest appearance.

episodes.name: Madonna: The Unauthorized Rusical
episodes.overview: The queens get into the groove in a Queen of Pop inspired musical. U.S. Representative Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez and supermodel Winnie Harlow guest judge.

episodes.name: Droop
episodes.overview: The queens must create and market ridiculously extravagant products for the new drag queen lifestyle brand, Droop.

episodes.name: Choices 2020
episodes.overview: It’s time for America’s first drag queen president! The queens argue in a fabulous presidential debate. Actors Jeff Goldblum (Jurassic Park) and Rachel Bloom (Crazy Ex-Girlfriend) guest judge.

episodes.name: Superfan Makeover
episodes.overview: The queens must give makeovers to drag race superfans, who have no idea what's about to happen to them; actor Daisy Ridley guest judges.

guest_stars.character: Self - Special Guest / Jazz Essence Hall
guest_stars.name: Bethany Akeroyd

guest_stars.character: Self - Special Guest / Lil' Snacky Cox
guest_stars.name: Tiffany Dela Cruz

episodes.name: One-Queen Show
episodes.overview: The queens must create and perform their own solo show; Whoopi Goldberg coaches the queens.

episodes.name: Viva Drag Vegas
episodes.overview: The queens must perform a medley of songs from RuPaul’s Drag Race Live!, a hit show on the Las Vegas strip. Choreographer Jamal Sims (Disney’s Aladdin) guest judges.

episodes.name: Alone Together
episodes.overview: The 12 queens come together in a virtual slumber party to kiki about all things season 12. Ru checks in with all the girls during quarantine and chats about the shadiest moments, most shocking eliminations and takes fan questions.

episodes.name: Grand Finale
episodes.overview: For the first time in herstory, the Top Three queens compete for the crown virtually in a final, epic lip-sync battle from their homes, featuring celebrity guests and past queens.

12.name: Season 12
12.overview: The twelfth season of RuPaul's Drag Race premiered on February 28 and concluded on May 29, 2020. The competition was broadcast on VH1 in the United States and saw 13 new queens competing for the title of "America's Next Drag Superstar".

episodes.name: The Pork Chop
episodes.overview: After making their werk room entrances, the queens face off in a series of Lip Sync for Your Life battles.

episodes.name: Condragulations
episodes.overview: After the first contestant of the season is voted out, the queens stomp the runway in a fashion show, then perform a special version of RuPaul's song "Condragulations."

episodes.name: Phenomenon
episodes.overview: The previously chopped queens return to walk in a fashion runway show, then perform a choreographed number to RuPaul's song "Phenomenon," and comedian Nicole Byer guest judges.

episodes.name: RuPaulmark Channel
episodes.overview: After the queens come together for the first time, RuPaul hosts a holiday movie marathon featuring Hallmark Channel-inspired parodies.

episodes.name: The Bag Ball
episodes.overview: Tensions rise as queens put their design skills to the test in a pageant of bag-inspired couture, and showcase three bag-themed looks.

episodes.name: Disco-Mentary
episodes.overview: The queens funk it up in a disco-dancing documentary, complete with 70s fashions.

episodes.name: Bossy Rossy Ruboot
episodes.overview: The queens flex their improv skills in a reboot of the salacious talk show "Bossy Rossy," hosted by Ross Mathews; LGBT activist TS Madison guest judges.

episodes.name: Social Media: The Unverified Rusical
episodes.overview: It’s time for the Rusical! Queens must record lyrics and learn choreography as they perform in a tale on social media. Choreographer Jamal Sims guest judges; Anne Hathaway (The Devil Wears Prada) makes a virtual appearance in the workroom.

episodes.name: Snatch Game
episodes.overview: The queens impersonate celebrities in the legendary Snatch Game. LGBT activist TS Madison guest judges.

episodes.name: Freaky Friday Queens
episodes.overview: It’s Freaky Friday! The queens are challenged to make over each other into their own drag doppelgangers. Comedian and host Loni Love (Soul Plane) guest judges; psychic Char Margolis makes an appearance.

episodes.name: Pop! Goes the Queens
episodes.overview: The queens must create and brand their own versions of extravagant soft drinks. Current reigning America’s Next Drag Superstar Jaida Essence Hall makes a virtual appearance in the workroom.

episodes.name: Nice Queens Roast
episodes.overview: The queens take part in a comedy roast of former Drag Race "Miss Congeniality" winners - Heidi N Closet, Nina West and Valentina. Comedian and host Loni Love (Soul Plane) guest judges; Norvina (Instant Influencer) makes a guest appearance.

episodes.name: Henny, I Shrunk the Drag Queens!
episodes.overview: The queens flex their acting skills in a new sci-fi adventure, playing tiny shrunken drag queens. Cynthia Erivo (Genius: Aretha) guest judges; Scarlett Johansson (Black Widow) makes a virtual appearance in the workroom.

episodes.name: Gettin' Lucky
episodes.overview: The queens write and record lyrics as they perform to the world premiere of RuPaul's new song "Lucky". Choreographer Jamal Sims (Disney's Aladdin) makes a guest appearance.

episodes.name: Reunited
episodes.overview: The season 13 queens are back to dish on all the moments that made this season unforgettable. This gag-worthy reunion will feature up close and personal interviews, original music videos, and a special lip sync.

episodes.name: Grand Finale
episodes.overview: It's time to crown our winner, baby! The top 4 queens compete in a finale lip sync smackdown in the race to crown "America's Next Drag Superstar." The queens also pick a Miss Congeniality.

13.name: Season 13
13.overview: The thirteenth season of RuPaul's Drag Race premiered on January 1 and concluded on April 23, 2021. The cast was announced via Twitter on December 9, 2020. The competition is broadcast on VH1 in the United States and showcases 13 new queens competing for the title of "America's Next Drag Superstar".

episodes.name: Big Opening No. 1
episodes.overview: Lizzo guest judges part one of the Season 14 premiere, and a new set of queens stars in a dizzying photo shoot, performs in a talent show and walks the runway in Signature Showstopping Drag.

episodes.name: Big Opening No. 2
episodes.overview: The remaining queens of the brand new cast bring their gifts to a talent show; singer/songwriter Alicia Keys guest judges.

episodes.name: A Pair Of Balls
episodes.overview: The queens put their design skills to the test in a Double Ball challenge, stomping the runway in 42 fashion looks. Christine Chiu (Bling Empire) guest judges.

episodes.name: She's a Super Tease
episodes.overview: The queens star in self-produced Season 14 teaser trailers, Jennifer Lopez sends the girls a message before the Night of a Thousand JLos runway, and Loni Love sits in with the judges.

episodes.name: Save a Queen
episodes.overview: First-eliminated queens from past seasons return to star in parody PSA commercials, the category on the runway is Spring Has Sprung, and singer Ava Max sits in with the judges.

episodes.name: Glamazon Prime
episodes.overview: The queens repurpose unconventional materials from Glamazon Prime shipping boxes into high-fashion runway looks, and Taraji P. Henson sits in with the judges.

episodes.name: The Daytona Wind
episodes.overview: The queens star in the over-the-top soap opera "The Daytona Wind" and serve Chaps on the Runway, and Ts Madison sits in with the judges.

episodes.name: 60s Girl Groups
episodes.overview: The queens read each other for filth, write and perform 60s girl group-inspired songs and pour their hearts into their runway lewks, and comedian Alec Mapa sits in with the judges.

episodes.name: Menzeses
episodes.overview: The queens must lead Drag Con panel discussions about the multi-faceted world of menz: dating, fatherhood, and toxic masculinity; comedian Nicole Byer guest judges.

episodes.name: Snatch Game
episodes.overview: The queens impersonate celebrities in Snatch Game; Drag Race royalty Raven and actress Dove Cameron ("Descendants") play the game.

episodes.name: An Extra Special Episode
episodes.overview: RuPaul introduces a twist that leaves the dolls gagging.

episodes.name: Moulin Ru: The Rusical
episodes.overview: The queens go to Gay Paree, in the romantic musical, Moulin Ru; singer Andra Day ("The United States vs. Billie Holiday") guest judges; actor Leslie Jordan ("Will & Grace") guest stars.

episodes.name: The Ross Mathews Roast
episodes.overview: Anastasia Beverly Hills President Norvina stops by as the queens paint the faces of RuPaul and Dolly Parton on a mural, Ross Mathews gets roasted, and Dulcé Sloan sits in with the judges.

episodes.name: Catwalk
episodes.overview: For their final challenge, the Top Five queens design costumes, learn choreography and write song lyrics for their music video debuts in RuPaul's "Catwalk."

episodes.name: Reunited!
episodes.overview: One week away from the Grand Finale, the contestants return to discuss the season’s gaggiest moments.

episodes.name: Grand Finale
episodes.overview: The final 5 must face off in Showgirl Showdown for $150,000 and the title of America's Next Drag Superstar.

14.name: Season 14
14.overview: The fourteenth season of RuPaul's Drag Race premiered on January 7, 2022. The reality competition series, broadcast on VH1 in the United States, showcases 14 new queens competing for the title of "America's Next Drag Superstar".

episodes.name: One Night Only, Part 1
episodes.overview: She's back again; the unbearably long wait is over as RuPaul returns with a brand new field of gorgeous and talented sequin-sporting queens.

episodes.name: One Night Only, Part 2
episodes.overview: A new cast of queens, competing to be crowned America's Next Drag Superstar, must show off their performance skills in a talent show; singer Ariana Grande guest judges.

episodes.name: All Queens Go To Heaven
episodes.overview: In this heavenly acting challenge, the queens must create infomercials for a queer afterlife. Country singer Maren Morris and LGBT activist Ts Madison guest judge.

episodes.name: Supersized Snatch Game
episodes.overview: Ru serves up a double helping of the celebrity impersonation game show, with the queens playing in two rounds, with two different casts of characters. Amandla Stenberg (The Hate U Give) guest judges.

episodes.name: House Of Fashion
episodes.overview: The queens must turn home decor into haute couture; actress Janelle Monae guest judges.

episodes.name: Old Friends Gold
episodes.overview: The queens fast forward 50 years to perform in old lady girl groups, singing about life, love, and growing old with your besties. Actress/ comedian Megan Stalter (Hacks) guest judges.

episodes.name: The Daytona Wind 2
episodes.overview: The queens exchange flatulence for canned joy, as the melodramatic act challenge returns in surreal sitcom form; actor Harvey Guillén guest judges.

episodes.name: LipSync Lalaparuza Smackdown
episodes.overview: Strategy and alliances emerge as the queens face off in a series of lip syncs, all leading to a final sudden death elimination round.

episodes.name: The Crystal Ball: Episode 200
episodes.overview: Drag Race celebrates it’s milestone 200th episode. The queens design outfits feature the 15th year anniversary gift: crystals. Julia Garner (Inventing Anna; Ozark) guest judges.

episodes.name: 50/50's Most Gagworthy Stars
episodes.overview: The queens get up close and personal with celebrities for TV's sketchiest newsmagazine, 50/50; the runway, category is Night Of 1000 Beyoncés; special guests Charo, Frankie Grande and Love Connie.

episodes.name: Two Queens, One Joke
episodes.overview: The queens perform stand-up comedy in pairs, but an odd number of queens causes for some drama. Comedian Ali Wong (Ali Wong: Baby Cobra) guest judges.

episodes.name: Wigloose: The Rusical!
episodes.overview: This season’s Rusical is set in the small town of West Bumtuck, where drag has been outlawed. An underground alliance forms to try and defeat the bigots. Country music sensation Orville Peck guest judges.

episodes.name: Teacher Makeovers
episodes.overview: The queens give drag makeovers to hard-working teachers, from kindergarten to high school. Queer pop musician Hayley Kiyoko guest judges.

episodes.name: Blame It On The Edit
episodes.overview: The final queens collab with RuPaul on a remix of his song “Blame It On The Edit,” recording their own verses and creating a space-themed music video.

episodes.name: Reunited!
episodes.overview: One week away from the Grand Finale, the queens return to discuss the season's gaggiest moments.

episodes.name: Grand Finale
episodes.overview: RuPaul crowns America's Next Drag Superstar in an epic battle for the grand prize of $200,000.

15.name: Season 15
15.overview: This season features the largest cast in the show's history, with sixteen queens competing and the largest cash prize, with the winner earning $200,000. It is also the first season to feature biological relatives, twins Sugar and Spice. Series judges Michelle Visage, Carson Kressley, and Ross Mathews returned, and Ts Madison, who had previously appeared as a recurring guest judge, joined the rotating judges panel.

episodes.name: Rate-A-Queen
episodes.overview: Part 1 of the epic two part premiere. A new cast of queens, competing to be crowned America’s Next Drag Superstar, must show off their performance skills in a talent show. Oscar-winning actress Charlize Theron guest judges.

episodes.name: Queen Choice Awards
episodes.overview: Part 2 of the epic two part premiere. A new cast of queens, competing to be crowned America’s Next Drag Superstar, must show off their performance skills in a talent show. Superstar singer Becky G guest judges.

episodes.name: The Mother of All Balls
episodes.overview: The two groups of queens meet for the first time. Tensions rise as queens put their design skills to the test in a pageant of mother-inspired couture, and showcase three mom-themed looks. Iconic fashion designer Isaac Mizrahi guest judges.

episodes.name: RDR Live!
episodes.overview: Live from Tuckahoe, it’s RDR Live! The queens are challenged to serve up laughs in a hilarious send-up of the iconic sketch comedy show. Actress and three-time SNL host Sarah Michelle Gellar guest judges.

episodes.name: Girl Groups
episodes.overview: The queens are tasked with writing and performing their own verses, for RuPaul songs from his new album Black Butta. Swedish synth-pop duo Icona Pop guest judge.

episodes.name: Welcome to the DollHouse
episodes.overview: After a flamenco dance with Spanish sensation Charo, the queens must design their own dolls, based on their drag personas. Superstar stylist Law Roach guest judges.

episodes.name: The Sound of Rusic
episodes.overview: This season’s Rusical is set high in the Swish Alps, as a young queen called Mariah goes in search of a musical outlet for her inner freak. Legendary director Adam Shankman guest judges.

episodes.name: Snatch Game
episodes.overview: After the iconic Reading challenge, the queens impersonate celebrities in the classic quick-fire comedy game show. All Stars winner Chad Michaels drops by the werkroom; actress Kyra Sedgwick guest judges.

episodes.name: See You Next Wednesday
episodes.overview: Morticia meets Mugler as the queens create a Neo-Goth look from scratch, using only black, white and gray fabric. Drop dead gorgeous model and actress Kaia Gerber guest judges.

episodes.name: Werq the World
episodes.overview: The queens let their voices be heard in an inspirational political anthem, and exercise their right to shake their groove thing. Choreographer Jamal Sims guest judges.

episodes.name: Corporate Queens
episodes.overview: The queens must devise and present comical Drag Awareness seminars in front of a live audience of corporate employees, and actor and comedian Joel Kim Booster guest judges.

episodes.name: Bathroom Hunties
episodes.overview: Nature calls as the queens star in the hot new design show "Bathroom Hunties," decorating and showcasing over-the-top powder rooms, and actress Mayan Lopez guest judges.

episodes.name: Drag Race Vegas Live! Makeovers
episodes.overview: Hunky male dancers from the RuPaul’s Drag Race LIVE! show in Las Vegas drop by the werkroom, to be made over into devastating drag queens. Country star Kelsea Ballerini guest judges.

guest_stars.character: Self - Dancer (as La Tina Love Dion)
guest_stars.name: Miguel Rivera Laureano

episodes.name: Booked & Blessed
episodes.overview: The queens dig deep to write their memoirs, pose for a book cover photo shoot, and get grilled by podcaster Matt Rogers, and journalist and author Ronan Farrow guest judges.

episodes.name: LipSync Lalaparuza Smackdown Reunited
episodes.overview: All the eliminated queens return to battle it out in a LipSync Lalaparuza Smackdown, with nine lip syncs and a cash prize of $50,000 on the line.

episodes.name: Grand Finale
episodes.overview: The top queens face off in an epic evening of performances and lip syncs, as they compete for the title of America’s Next Drag Superstar and a grand prize of $200,000.

16.name: Season 16
16.overview: The sixteenth season of Drag Race showcases fourteen drag queens competing for the title of America's Next Drag Superstar, a one-year supply of Anastasia Beverly Hills cosmetics, a crown and scepter from Fierce Drag Jewels and a cash prize of $200,000.
